{
  "story_text": "We find ourselves standing in the heart of the 'Laboratory of Perpetual Optimism,' a place that smells faintly of bleach and existential dread. Gloria is beaming, adjusting a decorative ribbon on a pulsating, neon-colored Arcane Interface that looks less like a scientific instrument and more like a disco ball fused with a toaster. 'See?' she chirps, her voice dripping with artificial warmth. 'We are finally ready to broadcast our gratitude frequency to the entire dimension. If we just align our intentions, the universe will have no choice but to provide us with the success we deserve!' ARK stands nearby, his face obscured by a glare from his monitors, busy mumbling instructions in broken German that neither One nor I can comprehend. He insists that this complex sequence of light pulses is 'tactically optimal,' though the machine itself is making a sound like a blender struggling with a brick. Donkey, currently posing near the Generic_Monster—a twitching, oily mass of static that he insists is merely an 'artistic installation'—is busy recording himself on his phone. 'A true knight never retreats from a challenge,' he declares, completely ignoring the fact that the monster just ate his lunch. One remains in the corner, clutching a UI design board, his eyes meeting mine for a fleeting second of shared, silent horror before he looks away, bowing his head back to his screen. The mission is simple: activate the machine to blanket reality in mandatory positivity. The cost? The machine is drawing power directly from the fabric of reality itself. Every 'positive' pulse weakens the foundation of this room, but Gloria insists that 'doubting the process' is the only true threat to our progress. She turns to me, her smile tightening just enough to be a warning. 'Everything is a blessing, isn't it? Just pull the lever.'\n\n[Cautious] Attempt to stabilize the energy flow before activating the machine.\n[Balanced] Suggest we test the machine on a small scale first.\n[Reckless] Engage the full power sequence immediately and hope for the best.\n[Positive] Praise Gloria for her vision and pull the lever without hesitation.\n[Complain] Point out that the machine is literally tearing reality apart.",
