{
  "story_text": "As I finally declared that the entire mission was complete, unadulterated nonsense, the lab fell into a deafening, pressurized silence. The cooling system, pushed past its breaking point by Gloria’s ‘spiritual’ adjustments, let out one final, mournful hiss before the main core simply ceased to be. ARK stood motionless, staring at the blank screen with the empty, vacant eyes of a man whose black-box reality had just been forcibly opened. Donkey, having spent the last hour attempting to craft a heroic narrative about the steam clouds on social media, finally realized he had no followers to impress in a dead facility. Gloria didn't even yell; she just offered a sad, patronizing smile, her eyes glimmering with the absolute certainty that my 'negative vibration' had single-handedly destroyed the divine project. As the emergency lights flickered and died, plunging us into the cold, dark reality of our absolute failure, the irony was thick enough to choke on: we had achieved perfect, absolute silence, just as they had always wanted. The mission was over, the machine was scrap, and the group was finally, irrevocably shattered.",
