{
  "story_text": "I whispered 'iloveu' into the freezing, steam-choked void of the lab, a pathetic attempt at human connection amidst the wreckage of our ambition. Gloria tilted her head, her expression shifting from sanctimonious pride to a terrifying, pitying softness. 'Oh, darling,' she cooed, reaching out to stroke my hair with a hand that felt like ice, 'you’re finally beginning to understand that true love is just the total surrender of the self to the collective harmony.' She leaned in close, whispering into my ear while ARK stood behind us, his eyes still vacant, his lips twitching as if he were trying to reboot his own reality. 'You screamed about this being nonsense before, but now? Now that everything is destroyed, you finally have the space to love me properly. Don't worry about the cooling systems or the ruin; they were just barriers to this moment of absolute, unconditional submission.'",
