{
  "story_text": "The laboratory is gone, yet here we stand in the 'Safe Zone'—a pristine, aggressively cheerful garden floating in a void of fractured reality. Gloria is radiant, beaming as if the total annihilation of our project was merely a 'cleansing of the lower frequencies.' She has tasked us with our next mission: 'Planting the Seeds of Harmony.' Apparently, by sowing these glowing, crystalline flowers across the ruins of our previous work, we will generate enough positive energy to permanently seal the cracks in the universe. Donkey is already posing for a selfie with a trowel, trying to frame the yawning abyss of the end-times as a 'dramatic backdrop.' ARK, meanwhile, is meticulously drafting a 400-page manual on the optimal soil pH for these flowers, ignoring the fact that the soil is literally weeping black ink. I pointed out that planting flowers in a dimension currently unraveling at the seams is, to put it mildly, an exercise in futility. Gloria’s face hardened, her mask of tolerance slipping just enough to reveal the sharp, predatory gleam beneath. She sighed, a sound that carried the weight of a thousand manufactured disappointments, and asked me why I insist on polluting our fresh start with such 'heavy' observations. One stands silently in the corner, his eyes pleading with me to stop, to just let them have their madness, but the sheer absurdity of it is suffocating. To 'succeed' here means to convince the void that everything is blooming perfectly, effectively accelerating the rot behind the curtain of our artificial paradise. The flowers are already beginning to pulse, and they don't look like they’re breathing life back into the world; they look like they’re feeding on the rot. [Cautious] Catalog the strange properties of the flowers before deciding to plant them. [Balanced] Divide the planting zones to maintain a semblance of orderly, scientific progress. [Reckless] Throw the entire bag of seeds into the void to see what happens. [Positive] Smile, thank Gloria for the opportunity, and plant the seeds with forced enthusiasm. [Complain] Refuse to participate, pointing out the obvious toxicity of the soil and the vanity of the task.",
