{
  "story_text": "My refusal to plant the corrupted seeds hangs in the air like a rotting odor. Gloria doesn’t explode in anger; she simply looks at me with that chilling, wounded expression of a saint betrayed by a sinner. She sighs, a sound that seems to drain the very color from the garden, and turns to Donkey, who immediately begins a dramatic monologue about the 'agony of the enlightened' while fiddling with his collar. ARK doesn't even look up from his soil charts, but I see him marking a red 'X' next to my name with a pen that leaves a trail of black, oily ink. The atmosphere shifts instantly; the bright, artificial sunlight turns a sickly, jaundiced yellow, and the glowing flowers begin to wilt, their petals curling into blackened claws. Gloria finally speaks, her voice a whisper of sharpened glass: 'If you cannot contribute to the beauty, perhaps you should consider whether you belong in the garden at all.' The ground beneath my feet begins to pulse with a rhythmic, sickly heartbeat, suggesting that by refusing to plant the seeds, I’ve only invited the corruption to take root elsewhere—specifically, beneath my own feet. One offers a brief, terrified glance toward me, then hurriedly starts planting with frantic, trembling hands, desperate to fill the void I left behind. I am now officially the team's 'negative energy' anchor, and the cracks in the sky above are widening.",
