  "story_text": "As I ripped the pulsing flowers from the earth, the garden let out a sound like a wet lung collapsing. Instead of revealing the hidden reality I craved, the soil beneath the uprooted stalks simply ceased to exist, leaving a jagged, hungry void that began to pull at our feet. The flowers didn't bleed; they turned into a fine, glowing dust that coated our lungs, making every breath taste like copper and forced optimism. Gloria didn't scream. She merely closed her eyes, clutching her chest, and whispered that my 'negative vibration' had just caused the garden to undergo an unwanted structural reassessment. Donkey, true to form, attempted to heroically shield her, tripping over his own cape and landing face-first in the growing chasm. ARK, showing the absolute peak of his tactical brilliance, began frantically adjusting his soil charts to accommodate the fact that the ground was now a non-Euclidean trap. One looked at me with profound, silent exhaustion; he knew that by 'ripping' the truth out of the garden, I’d only succeeded in making the illusion far more aggressive. The sky above is now a bruised, swirling vortex of colors that don't belong in nature, and the void is hungry for more 'positivity' to fill its hollow belly. We are, quite literally, sinking into our own delusions.",
