{
  "story_text": "The silence that follows my scream is heavier than the void itself. Gloria doesn't look angry; she looks pitying, her eyes glossing over with that practiced, saintly disappointment that burns worse than any fire. 'You are projecting your inner instability onto our beautiful work again,' she whispers, her voice echoing in the collapsing space. Donkey, who had been scrambling to his feet, suddenly freezes, his face contorting into an absurdly valiant mask of indignation as he tries to deflect the 'negative frequency' I've released. ARK remains hunched over his charts, scribbling frantically as if calculating the exact trajectory of my psychological decline, his pen tearing through the paper. One, meanwhile, has stopped planting entirely, his hands shaking as he stares at the chasm. The ground beneath us gives a violent, tectonic shudder; by labeling the garden a trap, I have seemingly triggered its predatory instincts. The sky shifts to a bruised, necrotic purple, and the pulsing heartbeat of the earth quickens, matching my own. My refusal to accept the beauty has, as expected, made the horror manifest; the 'safe' garden is now actively devouring the space around us, and the team is retreating into their respective bubbles of delusion to survive the fallout.",
