  "story_text": "Gloria freezes, her smile momentarily fracturing into something brittle and jagged before she smooths it back into a mask of serene, weaponized patience. She ignores the suffocating reality of the crystal tomb, choosing instead to interpret my denouncement as a desperate plea for her emotional labor. 'Oh, you poor thing,' she murmurs, her voice thick with practiced, syrupy concern that makes my skin crawl. She glides toward me, reaching out to touch my forehead, as if checking for a fever. 'I knew you’d struggle with this level of protection. You’ve always been so allergic to grace.' With a condescending sigh, she begins to hum that dissonant melody again, but this time it isn't meant to reinforce the cage; it’s meant to 'soothe' my 'outburst.' As she sings, the crystal walls hum in response, tightening and pulse-shrinking, effectively squeezing the air out of the room to 'stabilize the environment.' She winks at the team, utterly oblivious to the fact that we are suffocating, convinced she is teaching me a lesson in gratitude.",
