{
  "story_text": "As I scream about the psychological shackles, Gloria’s expression shifts from saintly patience to a wounded, soft-hearted melancholy. She doesn't raise her voice; she simply sighs, a sound that seems to vibrate the very crystals trapping us, making them grow thicker and more jagged. 'Oh, you poor, frightened soul,' she whispers, her eyes brimming with artificial tears. 'I hear your pain, and I know it stems from a place of deep, unresolved trauma. That is why I cannot let you walk away from the healing process just because you are scared.' She steps forward, ignoring the fact that the air is rapidly thinning, and places a hand over my mouth, not to choke me, but to 'gently filter out the negativity.' She then activates the Arcane Interface, but instead of overriding the containment, she sets it to a 'Harmony Loop' that feeds my panicked screams back into the room as soothing, ambient white noise. By 'helping' me process my frustration, she has successfully transformed our desperate cries for help into a serene, soundproofed symphony of compliance, ensuring ARK can continue his work in 'peace' without any further 'dissonant distractions.'",
