{
  "story_text": "We stand in the heart of the 'Sanctuary of Eternal Harmony', a crumbling ruin draped in plastic flowers and sticky, aggressive inspirational posters. Gloria is vibrating with a radiant, terrifying joy, her hands clasped tightly as if holding the very fabric of reality together. 'We are finally here,' she chirps, completely ignoring the fact that the floor is melting into a viscous, violet sludge. Donkey is busy attempting to mount a rusted 'Symbolic Beast' statue, his armor clanking loudly as he declares that his 'destiny is to save the princess of this dungeon.' He doesn't notice the beast is slowly beginning to chew on his cloak. ARK stands by the 'Arcane Interface,' tapping at the glowing, flickering runes with a frantic, systematic intensity that accomplishes absolutely nothing. He refuses to look at One, who remains tucked in a dark corner, his eyes pleading for a quick exit while he meticulously cleans his gear in silence. 'We just need to activate the Altar of Gratitude,' Gloria whispers, her eyes locked onto mine. 'It will cleanse all this negative, questioning energy and bring back the light. Don't you feel the potential for a fresh start?' The air tastes like ozone and artificial strawberries. Every time Donkey speaks, the room tremors; every time ARK 'optimizes' the interface, the walls weep a black, oily substance. The task is simple: trigger the Altar to 'align our frequencies.' It’s the ultimate GDA1 mission—guaranteed to optimize our collective soul into a heap of smoldering, sanctified ash. I look at the lever attached to the altar, which is currently throbbing like a diseased heart. Gloria smiles, a perfectly calculated expression that says if I refuse, it's my personal moral failing. One catches my eye, shaking his head imperceptibly. The reality index is fluctuating wildly, and the Void Entropy is waiting for the slightest push. [Cautious] Carefully examine the altar for traps before activating anything. [Balanced] Attempt to coordinate with ARK to stabilize the flickering interface first. [Reckless] Yell a battle cry and pull the lever to force the 'alignment'. [Positive] Smile back at Gloria and thank her for this beautiful, transformative opportunity. [Complain] Point out that the room is actively dissolving and we should leave immediately.",
